The Adamawa state police command has paraded 61 suspected criminals, recovered five AK 47 rifles, human eye and large ammunitions. The state police Commissioner Olubenga Adeyenju, at the parade Monday in Yola said, the criminals were apprehended for kidnapping, armed robbery, burglary, receiving stolen property ,criminal conspiracy and unlawful possession of human part. Olubenga further noted that two single barrel gun, one g3, one revolver pistol, 328 round of lives ammunition, 10 carriages, a Toyota vehicle, over N58,000 cash and a  tricycle were also recovered. He noted that the command at fufore, Maiha, Ganye, Gombi Mubi-North and Yola-North LGAs also nabbed 58 male suspects for kidnapping activities. The CP explained “following reports received by the command, the officers and men of the anti kidnapping unit/SIB and professional hunters succeeded in dislodging the criminals from their hideout in various areas of the state. “The command arrested one Bamanga Bello ‘M’ 28 and Iliyasu Shayibu ‘M’ 33 for unlawful possession of one human eye. ‘”Sometimes in the month of June, this year, the first suspect who happened to be a resident of Toungo, was confronted by one Umar Snu, to supply him with human eye for N500,000. “The said Bamanga Bello linked up with the second suspect, who is the resident of Kwami LGA of Gombe to bring it. “Upon  arrival the command operatives attached to Ganye Division, arrested them and recovered the human flesh (Eye ball). “The command fight against radical shila activities also arrested some in the state. Also 11 officers were promoted and decorated at the command. The Commissioner who read out the IG’s speech at the event, urged the newly promoted officers to ensure they merited their promotion with hard work and dedication to duties. 